The paper deals with the concept of regression depth, which is a geometric measure of how well a hyperplane fits a set of points in high-dimensional space. This is a topic that is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the computation of regression depth, which involves solving optimization problems and may involve techniques from numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the use of regression depth in clustering and classification, which are topics in data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.SI).
